<p>I think I'd like to see the compute_energy code broken apart into at least three parts: </p>

<ul>
<li>initialize() - compute integrals, generate initial guess, etc.</li>
<li>iterations() - contains the SCF iteration for loop</li>
<li>finalize() - stability analysis and normal finalize of SCF</li>
</ul>

<p>Stability analysis would live very early in finalize making calls to iterations as needed and then let the remaining code in finalize be executed. This would easily allow for integral reuse and other quantities.</p>

<p>Does this flow work for this?</p>

